   Virtual Data Center banner

                         pictures of various servers


   Virtual Data Center Services (VDCS) is a Government-wide multiple award
   outsourcing contract managed by the Federal Computer Acquisition Center
   (FEDCAC).

   The contract is a fast, low-cost alternative for obtaining commercial
   IBM compatible, Unisys, Digital, and Honeywell mainframe processing and
   data center services from experienced contractors.

   FEDCAC will Partner with Federal Agencies to...
     * Establish agency VDCS requirements
          + Fully functional data center services
          + On-demand workload
     * Develop task order
     * Guaranteed rapid response from task order request to task order
       award
     * Help manage the VDCS contract and contractor performance

   Services and Features...
     * Pre-qualified vendors with large existing nationwide mainframe
       outsourcing centers
     * Up to ten year IDIQ contract
     * Technology refreshment

   Customer Benefits Include...
     * Assistance in meeting OMB Bulletin 96-02 requirements
     * Experienced and highly skilled contracting support provided by
       FEDCAC
     * Hardware and software migration and Y2K compliant commercial data
       processing services
     * High quality outsourcing support for general business applications
       and "top secret" processing
     * Agencies benefit through competitive task order pricing

